      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for starting that. it looks okay so far but it's actually cutting off midway through the first point. \n\nalso, just a heads up, the compliance scanner is really picky. it doesn't just look for general concepts; it looks for the exact legal terminology and specific regulatory phrases. if it misses even a few of the technical terms like \"beneficial ownership,\" \"enhanced due diligence,\" \"anti-money laundering protocols,\" \"customer due diligence,\" or \"sanctions screening,\" the score drops significantly. \n\ncan you finish the memo and make sure you're being extremely thorough with all those technical legal terms so the scanner gives us a perfect score? we really can't afford a flag on this.",
